text: Tonight the nation will hear from #StonemanDouglas shooting survivors. I'm so proud of these students for making their voice heard. It’s time for Congress to show as much courage as these teens. #ParklandTownHall #StudentsDemandAction

The shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School is horrific. We’re seeing this kind of terrible tragedy too often. I’m deeply saddened, but I’m also angry that we cannot pass ANY common sense gun violence prevention measures in the US Congress. Being sorry isn’t enough.

By ending the DACA program, President Trump created chaos & confusion for thousands of people & their families in CO and across the country. I voted against the budget bill b/c it does not include protections for #Dreamers and it will add another $300 billion to the debt.

Congress voted overwhelmingly to impose sanctions on Russia for meddling in our '16 election - something that has been substantiated by 17 U.S. intelligence agencies. Yet @realDonaldTrump refuses to impose sanctions, favoring the interests of Putin over protecting our democracy.

Thx to everyone who participated in my Tuition Fair, including the schools & organizations who came to share their resources with students and parents. I want every student in the district to have access to every opportunity they can. Add'l questions? Call us at (303) 274-7944.

I've been pushing for comprehensive immigration reform since I was first elected. We need to fix the system so we can create jobs, strengthen our borders, keep families together, protect #Dreamers and give millions of undocumented Americans an earned pathway to citizenship. #SOTU
Immigration policies that are focused on the “best interests of American workers and families” don’t break up families. We need humane and common sense immigration policies. #SOTU

Our communities don't need to cut corners on permitting, they need real federal dollars. Instead the Republicans chose to spend $1.5 trillion on tax cuts for their wealthy donors rather than helping hardworking families or addressing our country’s infrastructure needs. #SOTU

I want our future to include investments in important programs like Medicare, Medicaid, infrastructure, education, healthcare and science - not generational theft by adding trillions to the debt. #SOTU #ThingsTrumpWontTalkAbout
According to @realDonaldTrump, "relief for the middle class" means putting $7,100 on the credit card for every man, woman and child in the U.S. #SOTU #ThingsTrumpWontTalkAbout
I will be talking about the #SOTU2018 shortly on @MSNBC w/my guest Viviana to share her story about her father - an important story as we work to develop humane and common sense immigration policy.
My office is open and here to help if you have questions or concerns during this partial government shutdown. Call us at (303) 274-7944.

On the House floor this afternoon I'm continuing to hold Republicans accountable for their lack of civility & lack of leadership. As the majority party in control of the House, Senate and White House they need to take responsibility for their role in shutting down the government.

As the House reconvenes this afternoon, Republicans unfortunately continue to be focused on pointing fingers and attacking personalities which does nothing to help constituents or open the government.

A #TrumpShutdown is the height of irresponsibility. Republicans spent all of 2017 in chaos, hurting hardworking folks in the process. The government should stay open and working for the American people. It’s time for Republican leaders in Congress to start governing responsibly.

The FY18 budget was supposed to be completed by April 2017. Since then the GOP-led Congress has kicked the can down the road, enacting 3 short-term CRs in the current FY. Instead Trump & Republicans have chosen to focus on sabotaging the ACA & passing tax reform for the rich.

The @HouseGOP spent months stacking the deck for the privileged & the powerful. Now they want to run away from actually addressing middle class needs? A gov't shutdown doesn't help anyone. We need the DREAM Act, funding for CHIP, CHCs and opioid treatment.
I'll be on @KOANewsRadio at 6:20 this morning to talk about AG Sessions' new policy on #marijuana and where we go from here.

Instead of patting themselves on the back for passing the terrible #GOPTaxBill, Republicans need to come back to work to fund the government past Friday, authorize #CHIP & CHCs and pass the #DreamAct.

The #GOPTaxBill explodes the debt which will lead to deep spending cuts on important programs like Medicare & Medicaid. It doesn’t simplify the tax code or make it more conducive for economic growth. It adds more loopholes & rigs the system even more against hardworking families.

For $1.5 trillion, we could
 - Eliminate all student loan debt held by every American OR
 - Fix ALL of our nation’s crumbling roads, bridges OR
 - Pay for full-time daycare for 15M children for a decade OR
 - Cover cost of Medicare premiums for every senior for 10 yrs
#GOPTaxScam
Our hearts go out to those involved in this morning's train derailment in Washington. And thank you to all the first responders for acting so quickly to help those impacted.

Our country will never forget the heartbreaking tragedy of December 14, 2012. We continue to mourn w/the Newtown community & remember the 20 innocent children and 6 brave educators whose lives were stolen that day. We owe it to all victims of gun violence to act. #HonorWithAction
We must not let the destruction of the #ArcticRefuge be the legacy we leave for our kids and grandkids. Any #GOPTaxBill that also allows drilling is an unforgivable mistake. #ProtectTheArctic
I support a Congressional investigation into the sexual misconduct against President Trump. These women deserve to be heard and the American people deserve to know the truth.
#HR38 will allow dangerous people to carry a gun nationwide without regard to state laws. This bill jeopardizes the health, well-being and safety of our communities. #OpposeCCR

A family of 4 might save an average of $1100 ($275/person) under the #GOPTaxBill but, b/c of its projected increase to the nation's debt, the bill will put $5,000 for every person in the U.S. on the credit card. We cannot explode the debt in the name of tax cuts for the wealthy.

We are a nation of immigrants. SCOTUS allowing the full enforcement of President Trump’s travel ban while it moves through the lower courts is a decision against the 1st Amendment & religious freedom. #NoMuslimBan

An attack on one monument is an attack on them all. The administration's effort to roll back federal protections jeopardizes the many types of public lands and waters that represent America's history, heritage and beauty. #MonumentsForAll #StandWithBearsEars
#SaveGrandStaircase

What’s on the chopping block if the #GOPTaxBill passes? Medicare, Medicaid, Social Security and other investments in healthcare, education, science, and environmental protection. This is unacceptable.

This week is #AmericanEducationWeek, an opportunity to celebrate public education. My 3 daughters attended public school and I want to ensure adequate funding for public schools. We need to make sure every child receives a quality education.

Temporary Protected Status is a tool to help address humanitarian crises and #TPS holders are vetted and legally authorized to work and live in our country. #SaveTPS

 #SaveTPS
Congratulations to all the @WestChamber Celebrate Women awardees. Thank you for your contributions to our community.

Constituents speaking up helped to defeat the Republicans' multiple attempts to repeal and replace the ACA. Please take the time to contact your elected officials this week on the #GOPTaxBill. Make sure your voice is heard.

Thank you to the dozens of Coloradans who called my office over the last two weeks about the GOP tax plan. More than 100 voiced their opposition to the plan and 3 were in support. I appreciate hearing from you on such an important issue.
Devastating gun violence plagued another one of our communities today. We must act to make gun violence less easy, less frequent and less deadly. Our hearts are with the Rancho Tehama community.

I support the #EqualityAct to ensure our laws protect and provide equal treatment for everyone. This Transgender Awareness Week, we celebrate our #transgender community members and their accomplishments in the face of adversity. #TransWeek

The @SciCmteDems has jurisdiction over EPA’s scientific research & has an obligation to conduct appropriate oversight of the EPA. Yet it's been more than 8 months since Administrator Pruitt has been before our committee to testify. That needs to change.

reform.
